# Daily Digest Bot - runs at 8:30 AM in the system's local timezone
# Install: crontab -e, then paste the line below (adjust paths as needed)
#
# Prerequisites:
#   - System timezone set correctly: sudo timedatectl set-timezone America/New_York
#   - Node.js LTS installed (find path with: which node)
#   - gogcli (gog) authenticated under the same user account
#   - .env file configured in the project directory
#
# Notes:
#   - The cd is required so dotenv can find the .env file in the project root
#   - Use the absolute path to node (cron has a minimal PATH)
#   - If using nvm, replace /usr/bin/node with your nvm node path,
#     e.g. /home/pi/.nvm/versions/node/v22.x.x/bin/node
#
30 8 * * * cd /home/pi/daily-digest-bot && /usr/bin/node dist/index.js >> /home/pi/digest.log 2>&1
